SIMPLE: anatifa
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Anatifa
<hw>A*nat"i*fa</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Anatif⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[NL., contr. fr.
<ets>anatifera</ets>. See <er>Anatiferous</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>An animal of the barnacle tribe, of the genus
<gen>Lepas</gen>, having a fleshy stem or peduncle; a goose barnacle.
See <er>Cirripedia</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ The term <xex>Anatif⟦ae⟧</xex>, in the plural, is often
used for the whole group of pedunculated cirripeds.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Anatifer</ent>⟦br⟧
